    • matchRegexPattern

      protected void matchRegexPattern(org.objectweb.asm.Label t, org.objectweb.asm.Label f)
      Emits code to test a string value against a regex pattern. The Pattern object and the candidate string must have been placed on the stack (and will be removed by the match operation). One of `t` or `f` (but not both) must specify a jump target.
      Parameters:
      t - where to jump if pattern matched
      f - where to jump if pattern NOT matched

    • matchPattern

      protected void matchPattern(Expression left, Expression right, org.objectweb.asm.Label t, org.objectweb.asm.Label f)
      Emits code to test a string value against a regular expression pattern. Exactly one label (t or f) must be non-null.
      Parameters:
      left - the Expression which produces the string value to be tested
      right - the Expression which produces the regex pattern string
      t - where to jump if pattern matched
      f - where to jump if pattern NOT matched

      right - the right-hand operand

    • logicalExpression

      protected void logicalExpression(Expression exp, org.objectweb.asm.Label t, org.objectweb.asm.Label f)
      Emits code to evaluate a logical expression. If the expression is binary, both t and f can be non-null. Otherwise, only one of the labels may be specified. TODO: it should always be only one or the other!
      Parameters:
      exp - the Expression
      t - the Label where to jump if the expression is true (if null, the code branches to f if the expression is false)
      f - the Label where to jump if the expression is false (if null, the code branches to t if the expression is true)
